  "local_port": 49126,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I keep getting dock connected on my Android, how do I get it off?",
  "response": "If your Android device keeps displaying a \"Dock Connected\" notification or seems to think it's connected to a dock when it's not, here are some steps you can take to resolve the issue:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Clean the Charging Port**\n- Dust, debris, or lint in the charging port can cause the device to mistakenly detect a dock connection.\n- Turn off your device.\n- Use a soft brush, toothpick, or compressed air to gently clean the port.\n- Be careful not to damage the pins inside the port.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Restart Your Device**\nA simple restart can often clear temporary software glitches that cause the issue.\n- Hold the power button and select **Restart** or **Reboot**.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Check for Physical Damage**\n- Inspect the charging port for any signs of damage, such as bent pins or corrosion.\n- If you notice damage, consider visiting a repair center.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Disable Dock Settings**\nIf your device has specific dock settings, disabling them might help:\n- Go to **Settings > Connected devices > Connection preferences > Dock**.\n- Disable any dock-related options.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Update Your Device**\n- Software bugs can sometimes cause false dock detections.\n- Go to **Settings > System > Software update** and check for updates.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Use Safe Mode**\nIf the issue is caused by a third-party app, booting into Safe Mode can help identify it:\n- Press and hold the power button until the power menu appears.\n- Long-press **Power off** and select **Safe Mode**.\n- If the problem disappears in Safe Mode, uninstall recently installed apps.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Factory Reset (Last Resort)**\nIf none of the above works and the issue persists, you may need to perform a factory reset:\n- Backup your data first.\n- Go to **Settings > System > Reset options > Erase all data (factory reset)**.\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Seek Professional Help**\nIf the issue persists despite trying all the above steps, it could be a hardware problem. Contact your device manufacturer or a certified repair center.\n\nLet me know if you need further assistance!",
